race.comment: GERRINGONG (11) has been rock-solid in her three runs back, just missing the mark. She's well-weighted here and ready to peak with Clark steering under the light load. Expect a bold sight. LINEBACKER (1) oozes class and carries the top weight to prove it. He was solid first-up in the G2 Tramway and backed it up with a sharp trial. The draw is awkward, but his talent will carry him far. MAYFAIR (5) resumes and has shown he's more than capable on his day. Draws sweetly, and two solid trials suggest he's forward enough to give this a shake. SABAJ (9) also returns and looks a promising prospect. Three jump-outs have him primed, and with Lane aboard from a soft draw, he's set to feature. SNOW IN MAY (12) has built nicely through two runs this prep and should be ready to fire. The wide gate is a concern, but with even luck, she's right in the mix.
